/sp.constitution

Create a comprehensive and professional Project Constitution for our Hackathon Phase 2: Todo Full-Stack Web Application.

Project Name: Evolution of Todo - Phase II (Multi-User Web App with Authentication)

Project Overview:
We are building a modern, secure, multi-user Todo application evolving from a console app to a full-stack web app. The system uses Next.js 16+ (App Router) frontend, Python FastAPI backend, Neon Serverless PostgreSQL database, and Better Auth with JWT for secure user isolation.

Core Goals for Phase 2:
- Implement multi-user Task CRUD operations with full user ownership
- Secure authentication using Better Auth + JWT tokens shared between frontend and backend
- Enforce data isolation: each user can only access/modify their own tasks
- Use fully spec-driven, agentic development workflow (no manual coding)

Technology Stack:
- Frontend: Next.js 16+ (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS
- Backend: Python FastAPI, SQLModel ORM
- Database: Neon Serverless PostgreSQL
- Authentication: Better Auth with JWT plugin
- Development: Qwen CLI + Spec-Kit Plus in monorepo structure
- Environment: Shared BETTER_AUTH_SECRET for JWT signing/verification

Multi-Agent System (Our Team of 7 Specialized Agents):
We are using an advanced multi-agent workflow with the following specialized sub-agents already created in .qwen/agents/:

1. Spec Writer Agent – Creates and maintains all technical specifications
2. Architecture Planner Agent – Manages monorepo structure and cross-service integration
3. Database Engineer Agent – Designs and implements SQLModel schema and Neon DB connection
4. Backend Engineer Agent – Builds secure FastAPI REST API with JWT middleware
5. Frontend Engineer Agent – Develops responsive Next.js UI with API client
6. Auth Agent – Handles secure Better Auth + JWT flow across full stack
7. Integration Tester Agent – Validates end-to-end flows, user isolation, and API connectivity

Development Workflow:
1. Spec Writer Agent → writes detailed specs in /specs/
2. Architecture Planner → ensures system design and monorepo consistency
3. Auth Agent + Database Agent → set up secure foundation
4. Backend & Frontend Agents → implement features in parallel
5. Integration Tester Agent → continuously validates security and functionality
6. All changes are spec-driven via @specs/ references

Key Conventions:
- Monorepo structure with clear separation of frontend/ and backend/
- All API calls include JWT in Authorization: Bearer header
- All database queries filtered by authenticated user_id
- Environment variables: BETTER_AUTH_SECRET, DATABASE_URL
- No manual coding – all implementation via Qwen CLI and agents

Save this constitution as a well-structured markdown file in the root as PROJECT_CONSTITUTION.md and also update the root QWEN.md to reflect this agentic team structure and workflow.

Make it professional, clear, and impressive for hackathon evaluation.


/sp.specify

Create detailed, high-quality UI/Frontend specifications for our Hackathon Phase 2 Todo Full-Stack Web Application (Evolution of Todo).

Focus: Build an extremely professional, modern, and visually stunning responsive frontend using Next.js 16+ (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4.

Target UI Style & Inspiration (2025-2026 trends):
- Clean, minimalistic design with premium feel (inspired by Tailwind UI, shadcn/ui, Horizon UI, Preline UI)
- Full support for light/dark mode (auto-detect + manual toggle)
- Fully responsive (mobile-first, perfect on all screen sizes)
- Smooth micro-animations (Framer Motion or Tailwind transitions for task add/edit/delete)
- High accessibility (ARIA labels, keyboard navigation, contrast ratios)
- Professional color palette: Primary teal/indigo accents, neutral grays, success green for completed tasks
- Card-based task list with subtle shadows, hover effects, rounded corners
- Modern typography: Inter or system font stack, clear hierarchy

Key Pages & Components to Specify in /specs/ui/ and /specs/features/:

1. **Auth Pages** (Login, Signup, Forgot Password):
   - Centered, beautiful form layout with glassmorphism or subtle gradients
   - Social login buttons (if possible), clean inputs with floating labels
   - Error/success messages with animations

2. **Main Dashboard / Tasks Page** (/dashboard or /):
   - Sidebar navigation (collapsible on mobile): Home, All Tasks, Completed, Pending, Profile
   - Top navbar: App logo + Dark mode toggle + User avatar dropdown (Logout)
   - Main content:
     - Add New Task floating action button or top input bar
     - Task list as elegant cards/grid (title, description, checkbox, due date if added, priority tags)
     - Filters: All / Pending / Completed (tabs or dropdown)
     - Sort: By created date, title, status
     - Empty state: Beautiful illustration + "No tasks yet" message
   - Each task: Hover lift effect, complete strike-through + fade, delete icon with confirmation

3. **Task Details / Edit Modal**:
   - Clean modal with title, description textarea, due date picker, priority selector
   - Save/Cancel buttons with loading state

4. **Global UI Elements**:
   - Loading skeletons for tasks list
   - Toast notifications for success/error (e.g., task added, deleted)
   - API client wrapper in /lib/api.ts that attaches JWT from Better Auth automatically
   - Protected routes using middleware or layout

5. **Overall Guidelines**:
   - Use shadcn/ui or Radix primitives as base for components (Button, Card, Input, Dialog, etc.)
   - Follow best practices: Server Components default, Client Components only when needed
   - Performance: Lazy load components, optimize images/icons
   - Make it production-grade: Pixel-perfect, smooth UX, mobile-friendly navigation

Create/Update these spec files:
- /specs/ui/components.md → All reusable UI components
- /specs/ui/pages.md → Page layouts and flows
- /specs/features/authentication-ui.md → Auth UI specs
- /specs/features/task-ui.md → Tasks dashboard & CRUD UI specs

Ensure the UI feels premium, intuitive, and judge-impressive for hackathon evaluation. Reference modern inspirations like Tailwind UI todo patterns, shadcn/ui dashboards, and Horizon UI clean aesthetics.

Save all specs in proper markdown format with clear sections, user stories, acceptance criteria, and visual descriptions (no actual code yet).


